The paper proposes a new method for performing Sparse Kernel Principal Component Analysis (SKPCA) and applies it to outlier detection. This involves using kernel methods and regularization techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves analyzing the validity of SKPCA, which could fall under cs.ST (Statistics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
